aa(lp126
VNow, what does this mean for our politics,
p127
aVfor our public services, for our government?
p128
aVWell I can't, in the time I've got, give huge numbers of examples,
p129
aVbut let me just give a few of the ways that life can change.
p130
aVAnd this is so obvious, in a way, because
p131
aVyou think about how all of you have changed
p132
aVthe way we shop, the way we travel, the way that business is done.
p133
aVThat is already happened; the information and Internet revolution
p134
aVhas actually gone all the way through our societies in so many different ways,
p135
aVbut it hasn't, in every way, yet touched our government.
p136
aa(lp137
VSo, how could this happen?
p138
aVWell, I think there are three chief ways that it should make an enormous difference:
p139
aVin transparency, in greater choice and in accountability,
p140
aVin giving us that genuine people power.
p141
aVIf we take transparency, here is one of my favorite websites,
p142
aVthe Missouri Accountability Portal.
p143
aVIn the old days, only the government could hold the information,
p144
aVand only a few elected people could try and grab that information
p145
aVand question it and challenge it.
p146
aVNow here, on one website, one state in America,
p147
aVevery single dollar spent by that government
p148
aVis searchable, is analyzable, is checkable.
p149
aa(lp150
VThink of the huge change that means:
p151
aVAny business that wants to bid for a government contract
p152
aVcan see what currently is being spent.
p153
aVAnyone thinking, "I could do that service better, I could deliver it cheaper,"
p154
aVit's all available there.
p155
aVWe have only, in government and in politics,
p156
aVstarted to scratch the surface of what people are doing in the commercial world
p157
aVwith the information revolution.
p158
aVSo, complete transparency will make a huge difference.
p159
aVIn this country, if we win the election,
p160
aVwe are going to make all government spending over 25,000 pounds
p161
aVtransparent and available online, searchable for anyone to see.
